cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision algorithms for interpreting scenes from a real-time video stream in the context of computer-assisted surgery systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for surgical phase recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a teacher/student approach for learning from a small dataset, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
